 (The \"What\")#How do you want the financial data to get into the app?":[27,32],"#Round 1 Questions#2. Features and Functionality (The \"What\")#How do you want the financial data to get into the app?#{1}":[29,29],"#Round 1 Questions#2. Features and Functionality (The \"What\")#How do you want the financial data to get into the app?#{2}":[30,30],"#Round 1 Questions#2. Features and Functionality (The \"What\")#How do you want the financial data to get into the app?#{3}":[31,32],"#Round 1 Questions#2. Features and Functionality (The \"What\")#What are the absolute \"must-have\" features for Version 1 (MVP)?":[33,42],"#Round 1 Questions#2. Features and Functionality (The \"What\")#What are the absolute \"must-have\" features for Version 1 (MVP)?#{1}":[35,35],"#Round 1 Questions#2. Features and Functionality (The \"What\")#What are the absolute \"must-have\" features for Version 1 (MVP)?#{2}":[36,36],"#Round 1 Questions#2. Features and Functionality (The \"What\")#What are the absolute \"must-have\" features for Version 1 (MVP)?#{3}":[37,37],"#Round 1 Questions#2. Features and Functionality (The \"What\")#What are the absolute \"must-have\" features for Version 1 (MVP)?#{4}":[38,38],"#Round 1 Questions#2. Features and Functionality (The \"What\")#What are the absolute \"must-have\" features for Version 1 (MVP)?#{5}":[39,39],"#Round 1 Questions#2. Features and Functionality (The \"What\")#What are the absolute \"must-have\" features for Version 1 (MVP)?#{6}":[40,41],"#Round 1 Questions#2. Features and Functionality (The \"What\")#What are the absolute \"must-have\" features for Version 1 (MVP)?#{7}":[42,42],"#Round 1 Questions#3. User Experience & Design (The \"How it feels\")":[43,44],"#Round 1 Questions#When you open the app, what is the very first piece of information you want to see on your dashboard?":[45,55],"#Round 1 Questions#When you open the app, what is the very first piece of information you want to see on your dashboard?#{1}":[47,47],"#Round 1 Questions#When you open the app, what is the very first piece of information you want to see on your dashboard?#{2}":[48,48],"#Round 1 Questions#When you open the app, what is the very first piece of information you want to see on your dashboard?#{3}":[49,50],"#Round 1 Questions#When you open the app, what is the very first piece of information you want to see on your dashboard?#Are there any existing finance apps, websites, or spreadsheets you’ve used that you liked or disliked? What stood out about them?":[51,55],"#Round 1 Questions#When you open the app, what is the very first piece of information you want to see on your dashboard?#Are there any existing finance apps, websites, or spreadsheets you’ve used that you liked or disliked? What stood out about them?#{1}":[53,54],"#Round 1 Questions#When you open the app, what is the very first piece of information you want to see on your dashboard?#Are there any existing finance apps, websites, or spreadsheets you’ve used that you liked or disliked? What stood out about them?#{2}":[55,55],"#Round 1 Questions#4. Tech & Scope (The \"Under the hood\")":[56,57],"#Round 1 Questions#Since you'll be building this with AI assistance, what is your preferred tech stack if you have one?":[58,72],"#Round 1 Questions#Since you'll be building this with AI assistance, what is your preferred tech stack if you have one?#{1}":[60,60],"#Round 1 Questions#Since you'll be building this with AI assistance, what is your preferred tech stack if you have one?#{2}":[61,61],"#Round 1 Questions#Since you'll be building this with AI assistance, what is your preferred tech stack if you have one?#{3}":[62,62],"#Round 1 Questions#Since you'll be building this with AI assistance, what is your preferred tech stack if you have one?#{4}":[63,63],"#Round 1 Questions#Since you'll be building this with AI assistance, what is your preferred tech stack if you have one?#{5}":[64,64],"#Round 1 Questions#Since you'll be building this with AI assistance, what is your preferred tech stack if you have one?#{6}":[65,65],"#Round 1 Questions#Since you'll be building this with AI assistance, what is your preferred tech stack if you have one?#{7}":[66,67],"#Round 1 Questions#Since you'll be building this with AI assistance, what is your preferred tech stack if you have one?#Is this strictly a desktop web app, or is optimized mobile viewing a priority for quick logging?":[68,72],"#Round 1 Questions#Since you'll be building this with AI assistance, what is your preferred tech stack if you have one?#Is this strictly a desktop web app, or is optimized mobile viewing a priority for quick logging?#{1}":[70,71],"#Round 1 Questions#Since you'll be building this with AI assistance, what is your preferred tech stack if you have one?#Is this strictly a desktop web app, or is optimized mobile viewing a priority for quick logging?#{2}":[72,72],"#Round 2 Questions":[73,120],"#Round 2 Questions#1. The UX & Animation Flow (The \"Nothing OS\" Vibe)":[75,86],"#Round 2 Questions#1. The UX & Animation Flow (The \"Nothing OS\" Vibe)#**The Infinite Scroll Concept:** You mentioned wanting the entire app to feel like one continuous webpage with structural motion and instant navigation animations (likely using a tool like _Framer Motion_).":[77,81],"#Round 2 Questions#1. The UX & Animation Flow (The \"Nothing OS\" Vibe)#**The Infinite Scroll Concept:** You mentioned wanting the entire app to feel like one continuous webpage with structural motion and instant navigation animations (likely using a tool like _Framer Motion_).#{1}":[78,79],"#Round 2 Questions#1. The UX & Animation Flow (The \"Nothing OS\" Vibe)#**The Infinite Scroll Concept:** You mentioned wanting the entire app to feel like one continuous webpage with structural motion and instant navigation animations (likely using a tool like _Framer Motion_).#{2}":[80,81],"#Round 2 Questions#1. The UX & Animation Flow (The \"Nothing OS\" Vibe)#**The \"Health Snapshot\":** For the immediate dashboard view, you want a holistic picture of financial trajectory. If you had to pick the **one main hero metric** at the absolute top of the page, would it be **Net Worth** (past/present) or **Remaining Discretionary Budget** (the day-to-day focus)?":[82,86],"#Round 2 Questions#1. The UX & Animation Flow (The \"Nothing OS\" Vibe)#**The \"Health Snapshot\":** For the immediate dashboard view, you want a holistic picture of financial trajectory. If you had to pick the **one main hero metric** at the absolute top of the page, would it be **Net Worth** (past/present) or **Remaining Discretionary Budget** (the day-to-day focus)?#{1}":[84,85],"#Round 2 Questions#1. The UX & Animation Flow (The \"Nothing OS\" Vibe)#**The \"Health Snapshot\":** For the immediate dashboard view, you want a holistic picture of financial trajectory. If you had to pick the **one main hero metric** at the absolute top of the page, would it be **Net Worth** (past/present) or **Remaining Discretionary Budget** (the day-to-day focus)?#{2}":[86,86],"#Round 2 Questions#2. **Data Ingestion & \"Diverse Archetypes\"**":[87,100],"#Round 2 Questions#2. **Data Ingestion & \"Diverse Archetypes\"**#**The Manual/CSV Process:** Since Australian open banking can be restrictive, CSV uploads are a smart MVP choice.":[89,93],"#Round 2 Questions#2. **Data Ingestion & \"Diverse Archetypes\"**#**The Manual/CSV Process:** Since Australian open banking can be restrictive, CSV uploads are a smart MVP choice.#{1}":[91,92],"#Round 2 Questions#2. **Data Ingestion & \"Diverse Archetypes\"**#**The Manual/CSV Process:** Since Australian open banking can be restrictive, CSV uploads are a smart MVP choice.#{2}":[93,93],"#Round 2 Questions#2. **Data Ingestion & \"Diverse Archetypes\"**#**Account Archetypes:** You want to track everything from neobanks to stocks and managed funds.":[94,100],"#Round 2 Questions#2. **Data Ingestion & \"Diverse Archetypes\"**#**Account Archetypes:** You want to track everything from neobanks to stocks and managed funds.#{1}":[96,97],"#Round 2 Questions#2. **Data Ingestion & \"Diverse Archetypes\"**#**Account Archetypes:** You want to track everything from neobanks to stocks and managed funds.#{2}":[98,99],"#Round 2 Questions#2. **Data Ingestion & \"Diverse Archetypes\"**#**Account Archetypes:** You want to track everything from neobanks to stocks and managed funds.#{3}":[100,100],"#Round 2 Questions#**3. Tech Stack & Google Stitch Integration**":[101,113],"#Round 2 Questions#**3. Tech Stack & Google Stitch Integration**#**Google Stitch:** This is a powerful choice for modern apps, especially when you want to handle secure data workflows, serverless microservices, and tightly integrated AI components without managing massive, clunky backend infrastructure.":[103,106],"#Round 2 Questions#**3. Tech Stack & Google Stitch Integration**#**Google Stitch:** This is a powerful choice for modern apps, especially when you want to handle secure data workflows, serverless microservices, and tightly integrated AI components without managing massive, clunky backend infrastructure.#{1}":[105,106],"#Round 2 Questions#**3. Tech Stack & Google Stitch Integration**#**State Management & Charts:** Recharts is great, but for highly responsive, \"structural motion\" dashboards, sometimes libraries like _Tremor_ (built on Tailwind) or _nivo_ offer cleaner minimalism out of the box.":[107,113],"#Round 2 Questions#**3. Tech Stack & Google Stitch Integration**#**State Management & Charts:** Recharts is great, but for highly responsive, \"structural motion\" dashboards, sometimes libraries like _Tremor_ (built on Tailwind) or _nivo_ offer cleaner minimalism out of the box.#{1}":[109,110],"#Round 2 Questions#**3. Tech Stack & Google Stitch Integration**#**State Management & Charts:** Recharts is great, but for highly responsive, \"structural motion\" dashboards, sometimes libraries like _Tremor_ (built on Tailwind) or _nivo_ offer cleaner minimalism out of the box.#{2}":[111,112],"#Round 2 Questions#**3. Tech Stack & Google Stitch Integration**#**State Management & Charts:** Recharts is great, but for highly responsive, \"structural motion\" dashboards, sometimes libraries like _Tremor_ (built on Tailwind) or _nivo_ offer cleaner minimalism out of the box.#{3}":[113,113],"#Round 2 Questions#**4. The AI Philosophy (Avoiding \"Slop\")**":[114,120],"#Round 2 Questions#**4. The AI Philosophy (Avoiding \"Slop\")**#**Context-Driven AI:** To avoid looking like a generic \"vibe-coded\" app with a random chatbot shoved in the corner, the AI needs to be deeply integrated.":[116,120],"#Round 2 Questions#**4. The AI Philosophy (Avoiding \"Slop\")**#**Context-Driven AI:** To avoid looking like a generic \"vibe-coded\" app with a random chatbot shoved in the corner, the AI needs to be deeply integrated.#{1}":[118,119],"#Round 2 Questions#**4. The AI Philosophy (Avoiding \"Slop\")**#**Context-Driven AI:** To avoid looking like a generic \"vibe-coded\" app with a random chatbot shoved in the corner, the AI needs to be deeply integrated.#{2}":[120,120]},"outlinks":[],"metadata":{"tags":["#Project","#finance","#projects/fin-app/project-doc"]},"task_lines":[],"tasks":{},"codeblock_ranges":[]},"smart_blocks:01_Projects/fin-app/System requirements - Brainstorm.md#Round 2 Questions": {"path":null,"last_embed":{"hash":"1esygwi","at":1780747115616},"embeddings":{"TaylorAI/bge-micro-v2":{"vec":[-0.05012601,-0.05932483,-0.00885464,-0.06507162,-0.06204543,0.04481403,-0.05295836,0.0315505,0.04352138,0.03011194,0.01838846,0.05489341,0.03245188,0.06110512,-0.00415577,-0.00240024,0.03221111,-0.00436356,-0.03605897,0.09145879,0.04377608,-0.05402194,-0.00250647,-0.04075351,0.03685335,0.01829122,-0.0345505,-0.08348851,-0.02444325,-0.23627815,-0.02552958,-0.02684018,-0.01220717,-0.04320431,-0.03945901,-0.03298124,-0.01477911,0.04637415,-0.00838991,0.0443796,0.01861935,0.08087884,-0.0313811,0.00356472,0.05935219,-0.06968056,-0.00071775,0.04651183,-0.02249611,0.0631285,-0.00605023,-0.03291435,0.03806409,0.01143