 tech stack if you have one?#{6}":[65,65],"#Round 1 Questions#Since you'll be building this with AI assistance, what is your preferred tech stack if you have one?#{7}":[66,67],"#Round 1 Questions#Since you'll be building this with AI assistance, what is your preferred tech stack if you have one?#Is this strictly a desktop web app, or is optimized mobile viewing a priority for quick logging?":[68,72],"#Round 1 Questions#Since you'll be building this with AI assistance, what is your preferred tech stack if you have one?#Is this strictly a desktop web app, or is optimized mobile viewing a priority for quick logging?#{1}":[70,71],"#Round 1 Questions#Since you'll be building this with AI assistance, what is your preferred tech stack if you have one?#Is this strictly a desktop web app, or is optimized mobile viewing a priority for quick logging?#{2}":[72,72],"#Round 2 Questions":[73,122],"#Round 2 Questions#1. The UX & Animation Flow (The \"Nothing OS\" Vibe)":[75,86],"#Round 2 Questions#1. The UX & Animation Flow (The \"Nothing OS\" Vibe)#**The Infinite Scroll Concept:** You mentioned wanting the entire app to feel like one continuous webpage with structural motion and instant navigation animations (likely using a tool like _Framer Motion_).":[77,81],"#Round 2 Questions#1. The UX & Animation Flow (The \"Nothing OS\" Vibe)#**The Infinite Scroll Concept:** You mentioned wanting the entire app to feel like one continuous webpage with structural motion and instant navigation animations (likely using a tool like _Framer Motion_).#{1}":[78,79],"#Round 2 Questions#1. The UX & Animation Flow (The \"Nothing OS\" Vibe)#**The Infinite Scroll Concept:** You mentioned wanting the entire app to feel like one continuous webpage with structural motion and instant navigation animations (likely using a tool like _Framer Motion_).#{2}":[80,81],"#Round 2 Questions#1. The UX & Animation Flow (The \"Nothing OS\" Vibe)#**The \"Health Snapshot\":** For the immediate dashboard view, you want a holistic picture of financial trajectory. If you had to pick the **one main hero metric** at the absolute top of the page, would it be **Net Worth** (past/present) or **Remaining Discretionary Budget** (the day-to-day focus)?":[82,86],"#Round 2 Questions#1. The UX & Animation Flow (The \"Nothing OS\" Vibe)#**The \"Health Snapshot\":** For the immediate dashboard view, you want a holistic picture of financial trajectory. If you had to pick the **one main hero metric** at the absolute top of the page, would it be **Net Worth** (past/present) or **Remaining Discretionary Budget** (the day-to-day focus)?#{1}":[84,85],"#Round 2 Questions#1. The UX & Animation Flow (The \"Nothing OS\" Vibe)#**The \"Health Snapshot\":** For the immediate dashboard view, you want a holistic picture of financial trajectory. If you had to pick the **one main hero metric** at the absolute top of the page, would it be **Net Worth** (past/present) or **Remaining Discretionary Budget** (the day-to-day focus)?#{2}":[86,86],"#Round 2 Questions#2. **Data Ingestion & \"Diverse Archetypes\"**":[87,100],"#Round 2 Questions#2. **Data Ingestion & \"Diverse Archetypes\"**#**The Manual/CSV Process:** Since Australian open banking can be restrictive, CSV uploads are a smart MVP choice.":[89,93],"#Round 2 Questions#2. **Data Ingestion & \"Diverse Archetypes\"**#**The Manual/CSV Process:** Since Australian open banking can be restrictive, CSV uploads are a smart MVP choice.#{1}":[91,92],"#Round 2 Questions#2. **Data Ingestion & \"Diverse Archetypes\"**#**The Manual/CSV Process:** Since Australian open banking can be restrictive, CSV uploads are a smart MVP choice.#{2}":[93,93],"#Round 2 Questions#2. **Data Ingestion & \"Diverse Archetypes\"**#**Account Archetypes:** You want to track everything from neobanks to stocks and managed funds.":[94,100],"#Round 2 Questions#2. **Data Ingestion & \"Diverse Archetypes\"**#**Account Archetypes:** You want to track everything from neobanks to stocks and managed funds.#{1}":[96,97],"#Round 2 Questions#2. **Data Ingestion & \"Diverse Archetypes\"**#**Account Archetypes:** You want to track everything from neobanks to stocks and managed funds.#{2}":[98,99],"#Round 2 Questions#2. **Data Ingestion & \"Diverse Archetypes\"**#**Account Archetypes:** You want to track everything from neobanks to stocks and managed funds.#{3}":[100,100],"#Round 2 Questions#**3. Tech Stack & Google Stitch Integration**":[101,113],"#Round 2 Questions#**3. Tech Stack & Google Stitch Integration**#**Google Stitch:** This is a powerful choice for modern apps, especially when you want to handle secure data workflows, serverless microservices, and tightly integrated AI components without managing massive, clunky backend infrastructure.":[103,106],"#Round 2 Questions#**3. Tech Stack & Google Stitch Integration**#**Google Stitch:** This is a powerful choice for modern apps, especially when you want to handle secure data workflows, serverless microservices, and tightly integrated AI components without managing massive, clunky backend infrastructure.#{1}":[105,106],"#Round 2 Questions#**3. Tech Stack & Google Stitch Integration**#**State Management & Charts:** Recharts is great, but for highly responsive, \"structural motion\" dashboards, sometimes libraries like _Tremor_ (built on Tailwind) or _nivo_ offer cleaner minimalism out of the box.":[107,113],"#Round 2 Questions#**3. Tech Stack & Google Stitch Integration**#**State Management & Charts:** Recharts is great, but for highly responsive, \"structural motion\" dashboards, sometimes libraries like _Tremor_ (built on Tailwind) or _nivo_ offer cleaner minimalism out of the box.#{1}":[109,110],"#Round 2 Questions#**3. Tech Stack & Google Stitch Integration**#**State Management & Charts:** Recharts is great, but for highly responsive, \"structural motion\" dashboards, sometimes libraries like _Tremor_ (built on Tailwind) or _nivo_ offer cleaner minimalism out of the box.#{2}":[111,112],"#Round 2 Questions#**3. Tech Stack & Google Stitch Integration**#**State Management & Charts:** Recharts is great, but for highly responsive, \"structural motion\" dashboards, sometimes libraries like _Tremor_ (built on Tailwind) or _nivo_ offer cleaner minimalism out of the box.#{3}":[113,113],"#Round 2 Questions#**4. The AI Philosophy (Avoiding \"Slop\")**":[114,122],"#Round 2 Questions#**4. The AI Philosophy (Avoiding \"Slop\")**#**Context-Driven AI:** To avoid looking like a generic \"vibe-coded\" app with a random chatbot shoved in the corner, the AI needs to be deeply integrated.":[116,122],"#Round 2 Questions#**4. The AI Philosophy (Avoiding \"Slop\")**#**Context-Driven AI:** To avoid looking like a generic \"vibe-coded\" app with a random chatbot shoved in the corner, the AI needs to be deeply integrated.#{1}":[118,119],"#Round 2 Questions#**4. The AI Philosophy (Avoiding \"Slop\")**#**Context-Driven AI:** To avoid looking like a generic \"vibe-coded\" app with a random chatbot shoved in the corner, the AI needs to be deeply integrated.#{2}":[120,122]},"outlinks":[],"metadata":{"tags":["#Project","#finance","#projects/fin-app/project-doc"]},"task_lines":[],"tasks":{},"codeblock_ranges":[]},"smart_blocks:01_Projects/fin-app/System requirements - Brainstorm.md#Round 2 Questions": {"path":null,"last_embed":{"hash":"1qihpq2","at":1780747644738},"embeddings":{"TaylorAI/bge-micro-v2":{"vec":[-0.05021723,-0.05944528,-0.0082061,-0.06526553,-0.06133575,0.04427213,-0.05267565,0.03168024,0.04407263,0.03020603,0.01899431,0.05604626,0.03242937,0.06112638,-0.00521117,-0.0022125,0.03229281,-0.00442012,-0.03612235,0.09157108,0.0437244,-0.05369184,-0.00201647,-0.04056105,0.036769,0.01843687,-0.03428067,-0.08339258,-0.02469775,-0.23600791,-0.0259312,-0.02683405,-0.01270523,-0.04296671,-0.03984088,-0.03324188,-0.01449951,0.04634896,-0.00729682,0.04523382,0.01826049,0.08046359,-0.03127559,0.00411011,0.05827602,-0.06957679,0.00028406,0.04644281,-0.02345044,0.06383873,-0.00675916,-0.0327474,0.03776224,0.01163992